      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE MAILER (4) was safely held in a much richer maiden fresh then ran a much-improved race out to a similar journey when beaten less than a length. Blinkers added and expected to go close. ANGEL'S GATHERING (3) resumed after a very long break and was midfield. Fitter for the run and extra trip a plus. Expected to be in the finish this time. MONSUN'S PRIDE (10) also resumed from a long spell of over 18 months when fifth and beaten less than two lengths. Will be far fitter and can improve sharply. PACKERS JOURNEY (7) has been thereabouts last few. Rates well on best figures. LADY OF STEEL (6) is a 58-start maiden who is rarely far away but can never win. Still rates better than the rest.",
